snippet: Dr. Rose, the Dallas County medical examiner in 1963, waged an unsuccessful battle to perform the autopsy on the assassinated president.
abstract: Earl Rose, the Dallas County medical examiner in 1963 who waged an unsuccessful battle to perform the autopsy on assassinated Pres John F Kennedy, dies at age 85.
lead_paragraph: Dr. Rose, the Dallas County medical examiner in 1963, waged an unsuccessful battle to perform the autopsy on the assassinated president.
